handoff contract is too narrow for Milestone 5. The repo documents a simplified mesh, one graph archive, and one metadata file, but the roadmap requires a fuller per-neuron bundle that can account for raw mesh, simplified mesh, skeleton, surface graph, patch graph, derived descriptors, and the versioned preprocessing choices that produced them. Without a centralized asset contract, later milestones will end up binding themselves to ad hoc filenames and partially duplicated script logic.\nsrc/flywire_wave/milestone13_readiness.py:1236:        for partial in variants:\nsrc/flywire_wave/milestone13_readiness.py:1241:                            [*partial[\"condition_ids\"], str(item[\"condition_id\"])]\nsrc/flywire_wave/milestone13_readiness.py:1244:                            **partial[\"parameter_overrides\"],\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:75:The repo already has local entrypoints for `simulate`, experiment-level comparison analysis, validation workflows, and dashboard packaging, but Milestone 15 is specifically about running experiments systematically instead of by hand. There is still no canonical batch runner that can take a normalized suite plan, expand it into deterministic work items, execute the required stages in order, persist intermediate status, and resume or retry safely after partial completion. Without a real orchestration workflow, every suite run will devolve into hand-written shell sequences, inconsistent skips, or forgotten analysis and validation steps, which defeats the point of this milestone.\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:78:Implement the library-owned batch execution workflow for Milestone 15. The workflow should consume a normalized suite plan, expand deterministic work items or suite cells, execute the declared stages in a stable order, persist stage-level status and provenance, and support dry-run plus resume-safe behavior for partial reruns. Reuse the existing Milestone 9 through Milestone 14 library entrypoints rather than shelling out blindly wherever a direct library API already exists. The first version may stay local and deterministic rather than introducing distributed scheduling, but it must make stage ordering, rerun semantics, and failure handling explicit enough that large suites stop depending on manual operator memory.\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:82:- Work-item identities, stage ordering, dry-run output, and persisted status semantics are explicit and stable so a partially completed suite can be resumed without reinterpreting prior outputs.\nagent_tickets/milestone_15_experiment_orchestration_ablations_tickets.md:84:- Failures, skips, and partial completions are represented explicitly rather than being inferred later from missing files or console output.\nsrc/flywire_wave/whole_brain_context_query.py:338:            \"available\" if query_family == LOCAL_SHELL_QUERY_FAMILY else \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/whole_brain_context_query.py:391:        query_status = \"available\" if selected_context_root_ids else \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/experiment_suite_packaging.py:1902:            \"partial={partial}, failed={failed}, blocked={blocked}, skipped={skipped}\".format(\nsrc/flywire_wave/experiment_suite_packaging.py:1907:                partial=counts.get(WORK_ITEM_STATUS_PARTIAL, 0),\nsrc/flywire_wave/baseline_execution.py:763:            if status not in {\"ready\", \"partial\"}:\nsrc/flywire_wave/milestone7_readiness.py:415:    elif coupling_bundle_status not in {\"ready\", \"partial\"}:\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_sampling.py:620:    partially_clipped = (~fully_in_field) & (~fully_out_of_field)\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_sampling.py:627:        \"partially_clipped_detector_count\": int(np.sum(partially_clipped)),\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_sampling.py:629:        \"partially_clipped_ommatidia\": [\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_sampling.py:630:            int(index) for index, clipped in enumerate(partially_clipped.tolist()) if clipped\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_inspection.py:684:        partially_clipped = int(projection.get(\"partially_clipped_detector_count\", 0))\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_inspection.py:688:        elif partially_clipped > 0:\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_inspection.py:697:            \"partially_clipped_detector_count\": partially_clipped,\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_inspection.py:1081:        partially_clipped = {\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_inspection.py:1082:            int(index) for index in coverage_mapping.get(\"partially_clipped_ommatidia\", [])\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_inspection.py:1092:                    partially_clipped=partially_clipped,\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_inspection.py:1231:    partially_clipped: set[int],\nsrc/flywire_wave/retinal_inspection.py:1235:    if ommatidium_index in partially_clipped:\nsrc/flywire_wave/coupling_contract.py:785:        return \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/dashboard_scene_circuit.py:447:        result[\"availability\"] = \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/dashboard_scene_circuit.py:451:        result[\"summary\"][\"status\"] = \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/dashboard_scene_circuit.py:1973:                    else \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/dashboard_scene_circuit.py:2080:        return \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/geometry_contract.py:1069:        return \"partial\"\nagent_tickets/milestone_11_hybrid_morphology_classes_tickets.md:199:Even if the earlier Milestone 11 tickets land, the repo still needs one explicit integration pass proving that mixed fidelity is a coherent simulator capability rather than a pile of partially compatible adapters. Without a dedicated readiness ticket, it will be too easy to stop once one surface root, one skeleton root, and one point placeholder can all run independently, while leaving behind hidden planner drift, broken cross-class routing, unreadable result bundles, or undocumented gaps between fidelity policy and executed behavior.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:192:## OPS-001 - `make verify` is not a reliable gate for `make meshes`\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:199:`make verify` is documented as the operator preflight before the FlyWire-backed pipeline, but the script is not authoritative for the next step it is supposed to protect. It can still dump an uncaught info-service exception after client construction, and it also downgrades `fafbseg` or local-secret-sync failures to warnings while still returning success. That lets operators burn time on `make meshes` after a misleading green verify.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:202:- [README.md:59](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/README.md#L59) tells operators to run `make verify` before preprocessing.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:208:Make `verify` fail by default when mesh-fetch prerequisites are not usable, and shape every subcheck into explicit operator-facing statuses. If partial verification is still desired, require an explicit opt-in flag and label the result as partial rather than printing “Access looks good.”\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:211:`make verify` exits non-zero when FlyWire mesh prerequisites are broken, including missing `fafbseg`, broken secret sync, or post-client info-service failures.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:213:The success path is only emitted when the prerequisites needed by `make meshes` have actually been validated, or when the operator explicitly asked for a partial check.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:216:Run `make verify CONFIG=config/local.yaml` in an environment with working CAVE access but without `fafbseg` or working secret storage; it should exit non-zero with a targeted fix message.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:217:Run `make verify CONFIG=config/local.yaml` with an invalid datastack or forced info-service failure; it should return a shaped error, not a traceback.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:218:Run `make verify CONFIG=config/local.yaml` in a fully provisioned environment; it should still exit `0`.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:227:Several operator entrypoints import heavy runtime dependencies at module import time, so a partially provisioned environment dies with raw `ModuleNotFoundError` tracebacks before any CLI guidance can be shown. The repo already has a canonical recovery path in `make bootstrap`, but these failures never point operators back to it.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:240:`make select`, `make meshes`, `make assets`, and report commands that depend on extra packages fail with concise messages naming the missing dependency and the bootstrap/install fix.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:246:In an environment missing `trimesh` or `tqdm`, run `make meshes CONFIG=config/local.yaml` and `make assets CONFIG=config/local.yaml`; both should fail without a traceback and should point to `make bootstrap`.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:256:The geometry preview command is the odd operator-facing report surface out: it hard-fails on the first missing mesh/graph artifact instead of writing a blocked summary that tells the operator which roots are incomplete. After a partial `make assets` run, that makes preview failures harder to diagnose than the repo’s other offline inspection commands.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:270:The command exits without a traceback for ordinary missing-artifact cases and tells the operator whether to rerun `make meshes`, `make assets`, or both.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:478:## OVR-003 - Remove the unused “partial arm plan” execution path\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:707:The suite runner exposes a `--fail-fast` mode that should stop scheduling after the first failed or partial work item. That branch is separate from the default resume path and is not exercised by current tests or readiness. A regression could keep launching downstream stages after the first failure, contaminating persisted state and review packages, while the existing orchestration tests still pass.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:711:- The executor has dedicated `fail_fast` break logic on exceptions and failed or partial statuses in [src/flywire_wave/experiment_suite_execution.py:334](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/experiment_suite_execution.py#L334) and [src/flywire_wave/experiment_suite_execution.py:349](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/src/flywire_wave/experiment_suite_execution.py#L349).\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:719:- With `fail_fast=True`, execution stops after the first failed or partial work item.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:728:## TESTGAP-004 - `make verify` has no stubbed regression coverage for auth, outage, or version handling\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:735:`make all` starts with `make verify`, and `scripts/00_verify_access.py` contains nontrivial classification logic for auth failures, transient materialize outages, `--require-materialize`, missing materialization version `783`, and fafbseg token syncing. None of that is protected by a local deterministic test. A regression could misclassify token failure as a temporary outage or allow the wrong materialization version through without `make test`, `make smoke`, or any readiness command noticing.\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/combined_tickets.md:738:- The setup docs make `make verify` part of the normal access check and `make all` entry sequence in [README.md:59](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/README.md#L59) and [README.md:88](/home/jack/Documents/github/personal/fly_neural_simulation/flywire_wave_repo/README.md#L88).\nsrc/flywire_wave/synapse_mapping.py:1343:        return \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/synapse_mapping.py:1345:        return \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/synapse_mapping.py:1356:            return \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/synapse_mapping.py:1359:            return \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/synapse_mapping.py:1370:        return \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/synapse_mapping.py:1372:        return \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/coupling_assembly.py:306:        status = \"partial\"\nsrc/flywire_wave/coupling_assembly.py:308:        status = \"partial\"\nagent_tickets/review_runs/20260405T152735Z/specialization/api_boundaries_and_coupling/stdout.jsonl:6:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_1\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,260p' Makefile\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"VENV_PYTHON := $(if $(wildcard .venv/bin/python),.venv/bin/python,python3)\\nPYTHON ?= $(VENV_PYTHON)\\nCONFIG ?= config/local.yaml\\nMANIFEST ?= manifests/examples/milestone_1_demo.yaml\\nSCHEMA ?= schemas/milestone_1_experiment_manifest.schema.json\\nDESIGN_LOCK ?= config/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml\\nM6_CONFIG ?= config/milestone_6_verification.yaml\\nM7_CONFIG ?= config/milestone_7_verification.yaml\\nM7_EDGE_FILE ?= config/milestone_7_verification_edges.txt\\nM8A_CONFIG ?= config/milestone_8a_verification.yaml\\nM8B_CONFIG ?= config/milestone_8b_verification.yaml\\nM9_CONFIG ?= config/milestone_9_verification.yaml\\nM10_CONFIG ?= config/milestone_10_verification.yaml\\nM11_CONFIG ?= config/milestone_11_verification.yaml\\nM12_CONFIG ?= config/milestone_12_verification.yaml\\nM13_CONFIG ?= config/miles